narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take Italian! The instructors are great and the class is structured really well. After 2 semesters, I already feel like I've made more progress in the language than I did in four years of studying Spanish!

It's an L2 language. It's easier than L1 in that we only cover half the units we covered in L1, but it's harder in that the grammar concept are much harder to understand and remember. I think if you've already taken L1, you might as well continue onto L2.
